   (:claim "note-strike with identical arguments produces identical audible effect (given identical instrument state)." :program "(note-strike 60 4 100)\n(note-strike 60 4 100)\n(display 'deterministic-audible-effect)" :invariant "∀ p d v. note-strike(p, d, v) is deterministic in current instrument state" :meta "Same-input-same-effect. Falsified by any hidden entropy in note dispatch. See book-of-sound ch04 (note events) and book-of-computing ch03 (determinism).") (:eng "Deterministic notes = replayable songs." :math "Function of (pitch, duration, velocity, state)." :cs "Pure event emission."))
